Pilot vs Plane



Aired on 03/08/2010, Narrated by Jonathan Aris



On 26 June 1988, Air France Flight 296, an Airbus A320-100, fails to climb and crashes into trees after performing a flyby during an airshow at Mulhouse-Habsheim Airport, killing three people. The cause of this crash remains in dispute.
